CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1780665075
OL,3,CPrime Minister apologises to the
OL,4,Cfamilies of Springhill victims
OL,6,F"While the circumstances in which the
OL,7,Fevents occurred were undoubtedly
OL,8,Fchallenging, it is the duty of the
OL,9,Fstate to hold itself to the highest
OL,10,Fstandard.
OL,12,F"The Government accepts and deeply
OL,13,Fregrets these findings, and recognises
OL,14,Ftheir gravity.
OL,16,F"On behalf of the Government, I want
OL,17,Fto apologise unreservedly to the
OL,18,Ffamilies for what happened and for the
OL,19,Fgrief and trauma that they have
OL,20,Fendured since the tragic deaths of
OL,21,Ftheir loved ones."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU}D@RO]
